name: Tuscan Grill Panini
author: Kraft
summary: Mix up weeknight dinner with this delicious alternative your family will love.
ingredients: ½ cup KRAFT Tuscan House Italian Dressing and Marinade, divided
2 (4 ounce) boneless skinless chicken breast halves
1 small zucchini, cut lengthwise in half, then sliced crosswise
½ cup KRAFT Shredded Low-Moisture Part-Skim Mozzarella Cheese
directions: Reserve 1 tablespoon dressing; pour remaining over chicken and vegetables in shallow dish
Stir vegetables and turn chicken to evenly coat both sides of each piece
Meanwhile, drain chicken and vegetables; discard marinade
Cook chicken and vegetables in skillet on medium heat 10 min
or until chicken is done (165 degrees F) and vegetables are crisp-tender, turning chicken after 5 min
Fill bread slices with chicken, vegetables, cheese and basil to make 2 sandwiches; brush outsides with reserved dressing
